cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

This paper deals with a control problem involving multiple agents and shared resources, which is a common problem in multi-agent systems. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the probabilistic control of agents, which falls under cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.LG (Learning). The use of automated decision-support systems and smart cities suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
